Description:
Act as a vital link in a digital transition that will help to position our international transportation company for future growth
Samskip is a global logistics company, offering transport and related services by land,
sea, rail, and air. We particularly focus on cost-efficient, sustainable, and environmentally
friendly transport. With an annual turnover of more than 700 million euros, Samskip is one
of the largest transport companies in Europe, with offices in 35 countries across Europe,
North and South America, Asia and Australia, employing around 1700 employees in total.
Are you the great Back-End Software Engineer we’re looking for?
As a Back-End Software Engineer you will focus on crafting, developing, and testing critical enterprise solutions and other custom application development projects. You will work on a variety of new projects, as well as maintaining existing applications when required and you're happy to share your programming knowledge to support your colleagues.The application stack includes software to support the front-end user experience, business logic, back-end and database services. Appropriate use of software design patterns, architectural styles such as microservices are key tools to a Back-End Software Engineer. Specific responsibilities in this position:
problems and power enterprise-scale systems;
database design, data access and ORMs;
containerization, and automated testing;
working in a team with other developers, designers, and architects;

WHAT A TYPICAL DAY MIGHT INCLUDE
Work closely with data analysts in order to build and validate the data model;
Develop the processing flows using a generic Spark ETL tool or SQL statements;
Document the technical steps taken;
Push for new approaches which increase the efficiency of the team;
Raise the knowledge level of the team by sharing key details about big data technologies and tools.
EXPERIENCE & SKILLS NEEDED
SQL, distributed processing (Hadoop, Spark);

We are looking for an experienced Data Engineer to join our team and work with Google Cloud Platform (GCP). As a Data Engineer, you will be responsible for designing, building, and maintaining our data infrastructure and systems, ensuring their reliability, scalability, and performance. You will work closely with our clients, data analysts, scientists, and stakeholders to understand their data requirements and provide solutions that enable them to leverage the power of our data. This role is suitable for someone with regular to senior knowledge in data engineering, cloud computing, and software development.
Our promise:
You choose how you'll work with us: remote first or at our offices in Timpuri Noi Square (Bucharest) or Brasov;
We support your career growth through continuous learning, coaching, and mentorship programs;

WHAT A TYPICAL DAY MIGHT INCLUDE
As part of a development team, collaborate with other team members to understand requirements, analyze and refine stories, design solutions, implement them, test them and support them in production;
Develop and deploy, within a team, big data anti-fraud detection solutions and models using Python and PySpark; ability/willingness to learn how to improve them with machine learning algorithms and models;
Write code and write it well. Use test driven development, write clean code and refactor constantly;
Design and develop excellent and understandable server-side code;
Develop or being willing to learn big data machine learning solutions;

WHAT A TYPICAL DAY MIGHT INCLUDE
As part of a development team, collaborate with other team members to understand requirements, analyze and refine stories, design solutions, implement them, test them and support them in production;
Develop and deploy, within a team, big data anti-fraud detection solutions and models using Python and PySpark; ability/willingness to learn how to improve them with machine learning algorithms and models;
Write code and write it well. Use test driven development, write clean code and refactor constantly;
Design and develop excellent and understandable server-side code;
Develop or being willing to learn big data machine learning solutions;

Responsibilities
As a Data Engineer in Endava, you will:
Take part in all application development lifecycle phase;
Participate in logical and physical design of the product and understand the business requirements;
Solve complex technical problems that other team members may encounter
Propose solutions for the cloud-based architecture and deployment flow;
Design and build processes, data transformation and metadata that will meet business requirements and platform needs;

Requirements/Skills:
2-4 years of experience working in a cloud data engineer role;
Hands on experience with Azure Data Lake, Azure Data Factory, SQL Data Warehouse Azure Blob, Azure Storage Explorer;
Good to have knowledge on Power BI in Report development, Data Modelling;
Proficient in creating Azure Data Factory pipelines for ETL processing; copy activity, custom Azure development etc;
Design and develop batch and real-time streaming of data loads to data warehouse systems;
Good technical knowledge in Microsoft SQL Server;
Experience building data ingestion pipelines for a cloud, with data consumable by business intelligence solutions (e. g. PowerBI) and/or data scientists;

What will you do each day-

Technical skills:
At least 5 years of relevant work experience in data engineering and data operations;
Hands-on experience with handling different file types (CSV, XLSX, JSON, TXT) in Python;
Proficient in using the Django framework for data modeling and SQL transformations (DDL generation of data sources, script generation and logging);
Good knowledge of the AWS data stack and services (such as S3, Lambda and RDS);
Familiarity with planning, implementing and correctly executing the scheduling of the ETL flows to ensure they fit in the overall data platform design;
Familiarity with Confluence and Jira;

This is an excellent opportunity to join a fast-paced, dynamic team and make a significant impact on the success of our organization. If you are passionate about data engineering and have a track record of success in building data pipelines on AWS using the Django framework, we encourage you to apply. The main objective of the data engineer is to build the framework that supports the entire lifecycle of data-driven products through data pipelines. This means you develop the ETL flows to efficiently retrieve the necessary data from various sources, transform data according to the pre-defined business logic and eventually integrate data into the data platform. Data quality and robustness of the ETL processes are of great importance here.

Next to that, you will also participate in the further development of the data platform, which provides data and insights to various business stakeholders. Benefits:

